<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>MTG {{format_name}}</title>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/keyrune@latest/css/keyrune.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />

  <style type="text/css">
    body {
      font-size: large;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0 1rem;
      color: rgba(0,0,0,0.9);
    }
    .page-wrapper {
      max-width: 28rem;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 1em 0 3em 0;
    }
    h1, h2, h3, h4 {
      margin-top: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    p, ul{
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    p {
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    ul {
      margin-top: 0.3rem;
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
    }
    li {
      margin-top: 0.2rem;
      list-style: none;
      text-indent: -0.6rem;
    }
    .icon-list {
        padding-left: 2.75rem;
    }
    .icon-list li {
      text-indent: -1.85rem;
    }
    li > * {
      text-indent: initial;
    }
    li::before {
      content: "\b7";
      margin-right: 0.3rem;
    }
    a {
      color: inherit;
    }
    sup {
      vertical-align: baseline;
      position: relative;
      top: -0.4rem;
    }
    .icon-list .ss {
      display: inline-block;
      width: 1em;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .ss.ss-none::before {
      content: "";
    }
    .no-wrap {
      display:inline-block;
    }
    .header-section {
      text-align: center;
    }
    .fill-line-wrapper {
      white-space: nowrap;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .fill-line-wrapper h3 {
      display: inline-block;
    }
    .fill-line {
      display: inline-block;
      width: 100%;
      height: 1px;
      background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0.8);
      margin-left: 0.15em;
    }
    .footer {
      margin-top: 2em;
      text-align: center;
      color: rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
    }
    .column-container {
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .header-caption {
      display: inline-block;
      max-width: 28rem;
    }

    @media screen and (min-width: 48rem) {
      .page-wrapper {
        max-width: 46rem;
      }
      .column-container {
        margin-top: 2rem;
        display: flex;
      }
      .column-section {
        padding-left: 1rem;
        padding-right: 1rem;
        flex-basis: 1px;
        flex-grow: 1;
        flex-shrink: 0;
      }
      .column-section:first-child {
        margin-left: -1rem;
      }
      .column-section:last-child {
        margin-right: -1rem;
      }
      .column-section .fill-line-wrapper {
        text-align: center;
      }
      .column-section h3 {
        margin-top: 0;
      }
      .column-section .fill-line {
        display: none;
      }
    }
  </style>

</head>
<body>
<div class="page-wrapper">

  <div class="header-section">
    <p class="header-caption">
      {{#is_standard}}
      <em>Standard</em> is a competitive <em class="no-wrap">Magic: the Gathering</em> format which only allows cards from recent <span class="no-wrap"><em>Standard-legal<sup><a href="#details">&dagger;</a></sup></em> sets.</span>
      {{/is_standard}}
      {{#is_brawl}}
      <em>Brawl</em> is a <em>Commander</em>-like <em class="no-wrap">Magic: the Gathering</em> format which only allows cards from recent <span class="no-wrap"><em>Standard-legal<sup><a href="#details">&dagger;</a></sup></em> sets.</span>
      {{/is_brawl}}
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="column-container">

    <div class="column-section">
      <div class="fill-line-wrapper">
          <h3>Currently in {{format_name}}</h3>
        <span class="fill-line"></span>
      </div>
      <p>These sets are in {{format_name}}:</p>
      <ul class="icon-list">
        {{#current_sets}}
        <li><i class="ss ss-{{code}}"></i> <em>{{name}}</em></li>
        {{/current_sets}}
      </ul>
      {{#has_banned_cards}}
      <p>These cards are banned:</p>
      <ul class="icon-list">
        {{#banned_cards}}
        <li><i class="ss ss-{{set}}"></i> <em><a href="{{url}}" target="_blank">{{name}}</a></em></li>
        {{/banned_cards}}
      </ul>
      {{/has_banned_cards}}
    </div>

    <div class="column-section">
      <div class="fill-line-wrapper">
        <h3><!--Recent & -->Upcoming Changes</h3>
        <span class="fill-line"></span>
      </div>
      <!--
      <p>
        Most of the upcoming {{format_name}} products for 2020 have already been announced by <em class="no-wrap">Wizards of the Coast</em>.
      </p>
      -->
      <p>These sets will be added to {{format_name}} on release:</p>
      <ul class="icon-list">
        {{#upcoming_sets}}
        <li><i class="ss ss-{{code}}"></i> <em>{{name}}</em> <span class="no-wrap">({{release_date}})</span></li>
        {{/upcoming_sets}}
      </ul>
      <!--<p>
      Cards from <em>Theros: Beyond Death</em> <span class="no-wrap">pre-release</span> events cannot be used in {{format_name}} until the set is officially released on January 24.
      </p>-->
      {{#has_upcoming_rotation}}
      <p>
        The {{upcoming_rotation.rotation_year}} rotation will coincide with the release of <em class="no-wrap">{{upcoming_rotation.trigger_set}}</em> <span class="no-wrap">({{upcoming_rotation.trigger_time}})</span>.
        <br />
        These sets will rotate out of {{format_name}}:
      </p>
      <ul class="icon-list">
        {{#upcoming_rotation.rotating_sets}}
        <li><i class="ss ss-{{code}}"></i> <em>{{name}}</em></li>
        {{/upcoming_rotation.rotating_sets}}
      </ul>
      {{/has_upcoming_rotation}}
      <!--
      <p>These sets will remain in {{format_name}}:</p>
      <ul class="icon-list">
        <li><!--
       ---<i class="ss ss-eld"></i>
          <em>Throne of Eldraine</em>
        <li><!--
       ---<i class="ss ss-???"></i>
          <em>Theros: Beyond Death</em>
        </li>
        <li><!--
       ---<i class="ss ss-???"></i>
          <em>Ikoria: Lair of Behemoths</em>
        </li>
        <li><!--
       ---<i class="ss ss-???"></i>
          <em>Core Set 2021</em>
        </li>
        <li><!--
       ---<i class="ss ss-???"></i>
          <em>Zendikar Rising</em>
        </li>
        </li>
      </ul>-->
    </div>

  </div>

  <a name="details"></a>
  <div class="fill-line-wrapper">
    <h3>Details</h3>
    <span class="fill-line"></span>
  </div>
  <p>
    Each year, four "Standard-legal" sets are released by <em>Wizards of the Coast</em>.
    {{#is_brawl}}
    <br />
    <em>(Standard is a Magic: the Gathering format which Brawl is based on.)</em>
    {{/is_brawl}}
  </p>
  <p>
    These sets are added to {{format_name}} on release, and are removed from {{format_name}} after two "rotations".
    Rotations are annual, coinciding with the release of the fall set in September or October.
    This means each set remains in {{format_name}} for <span class="no-wrap">15-24</span> months.
  </p>
  <p>
    Any copy of a legal card can be included in a {{format_name}} deck, even if that copy is from an older set.
    For instance, a {{format_name}} deck may include a 1998 copy of <a href="https://scryfall.com/card/usg/132/duress" target="_blank">Duress</a>
    from <em>Urza's Saga</em>, because <a href="https://scryfall.com/card/m20/97/duress" target="_blank">Duress</a>
    was also included in <em>Core Set 2020</em>.
  </p>
  <p>
    Full rules for {{format_name}} are available on the official Magic: the Gathering website
    {{#is_standard}}
    <a href="https://magic.wizards.com/en/content/standard-formats-magic-gathering" target="_blank">here</a>.
    {{/is_standard}}
    {{#is_brawl}}
    <a href="https://magic.wizards.com/en/game-info/gameplay/formats/brawl" target="_blank">here</a>.
    {{/is_brawl}}
    </p>

  <div class="fill-line-wrapper">
    <h3>What to Buy</h3>
    <span class="fill-line"></span>
  </div>
  <p>
    Most players recommend buying individual {{format_name}} cards from a local game store or online seller.
    You can also open booster packs or play in draft or pre-release events for the Standard-legal sets listed above.
  </p>
  <!--<p>
    The most recent <em>Challenger Decks</em> contain cards from <em>Ixalan</em> through <em>Guilds of Ravnica</em> and are designed
    to provide a competitive Standard experience out-of-the-box.
    {{#is_brawl}}
    These decks also contain many useful cards for Brawl decks.
    {{/is_brawl}}
  </p>-->
  {{#is_brawl}}
  <p>
    Beginning with <em>Throne of Eldraine</em>, pre-constructed Brawl decks are available.
    These decks are designed to be playable out-of-the-box, and contain exclusive cards that will be useful in a variety of Brawl decks.
  </p>
  {{/is_brawl}}
  <p>
    The beginner-oriented <em>Welcome Decks</em> (which are given away by game stores) and <em>Planeswalker Decks</em> (for the sets listed above)
    also contain cards that can be used in {{format_name}}.
  </p>

  <div class="fill-line-wrapper">
    <h3>Non-{{format_name}} Sets</h3>
    <span class="fill-line"></span>
  </div>
  <p>
    Some sets are not Standard-legal, and are not added to {{format_name}} on release.
    Most or all of the included cards are not usable in {{format_name}}.
  </p>
  <p>Recent sets which are not Standard-legal include:</p>
  <ul class="icon-list">
    <li><!--
   --><i class="ss ss-none"></i>
      <em>Guild Kit</em> Preconstructed Decks
