  <ul class="icon-list">
  </ul>-->

  <div class="fill-line-wrapper">
    <h3>Related Formats</h3>
    <span class="fill-line"></span>
  </div>
  {{#is_standard}}
  <p>
    <em>Brawl</em> is a format which uses the same Standard-legal set rotation as Standard.
    Brawl is often played casually with 3 or more players per game, and uses different rules for deck construction and gameplay.
    <br />
    Read more about Brawl on the offical Magic: the Gathering website <a href="https://magic.wizards.com/en/game-info/gameplay/formats/brawl" target="_blank">here</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    <em>Pioneer</em> is a format which allows cards from any Standard-legal set released since 2012's <em>Return to Ravnica</em>.
    Every card added to Standard is also added to Pioneer, and cards never rotate out, though more cards are included on the banlist.
    <br />
    Read more about Pioneer on the official Magic: the Gathering website
    <a href="https://magic.wizards.com/en/game-info/gameplay/formats/pioneer" target="_blank">here</a>.
  <p>
    <em>Modern</em> is similar to Pioneer, but allows cards from any Standard-Legal set released since 2003's <em>8th Edition</em>, as well as the <span class="no-wrap">non-Standard-legal</span> set <em>Modern Horizons</em>.
    <br />
    Read more about Modern on the official Magic: the Gathering website
    <a href="https://magic.wizards.com/en/game-info/gameplay/formats/modern" target="_blank">here</a>.
  </p>
  {{/is_standard}}
  {{#is_brawl}}
  <p>
    <em>Standard</em> is a format which uses the same Standard-legal set rotation as Brawl.
    Standard is played competitively, <span class="no-wrap">1-versus-1</span>, and uses different rules for deck construction and gameplay.
    <br />
    Read more about Standard on the official Magic: the Gathering website 
    <a href="https://magic.wizards.com/en/content/standard-formats-magic-gathering" target="_blank">here</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    <em>Commander</em> is the other format on which Brawl is based.
    Commander allows cards from every Magic: the Gathering set ever printed, and features 100-card decks and other gameplay changes.
    <br />
    The official Commander website is <a href="http://mtgcommander.net" target="_blank">mtgcommander.net</a>.
    <br />
    Read more about Commander on the official Magic: the Gathering website
    <a href="https://magic.wizards.com/en/content/commander-format" target="_blank">here</a>.
  </p>
  {{/is_brawl}}

